<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-702-451  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 702 451.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Dec 17 1990 v36 n1840 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>De Castro leaving Data General. (Edson de Castro)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stedman, Craig.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Data General Corp's Chmn Edson de Castro and Vice-Chmn HerbertRichman resigned under pressure from the board of directors.andP;  Theco-founders agreed to leave in 1990 and 1991 respectively aftercreating the computer company in 1968.andP;  Industry observers notedthat the ousting of the co-founders was at the behest of RonaldSkates, president and CEO since 1989.andP;  Skates has been in controlof the company since he took office in 1989 and De Castro has beenlimited to playing a token role in policy decisions.andP;  Theydisagreed over a number of policies, including expenditures onresearch and development.andP;  The removal of De Castro and Richmanshould eventually save the computer maker, which has beenoperating in the red between 1985 and 1990, about $1 million insalaries and bonuses despite generous severance packages.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Data General Corp. (Officials and employees).andO;Ticker:    DGN.andO;Topic:     Computer industryResignationExecutiveChairmenBoard of Directors.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Edson de Castro, Herbert Richman. (portrait)Person:    De Castro, Edson (Resignation, retirement, etc.); Richman, Herbert(Resignation, retirement, etc.).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>